@section How to do funny realtime effects with glame

So, here you are. Imagine your giving a big party at home and you really want
to impress Angelina, Heather and all the other nice girls. And certainly you 
will invite the Glame Team, won't you? O.K. enough joking, now for the serious part. 
To have all that fun, you need to connect a microphone to your soundcard. 
Then fire up Glame and make sure you have the right preferences set up for your 
audio hardware (@pxref{The Preferences Dialog}). You'll need two 
soundcards for this kind of fun or in general one device for sampling and one for playback. 
Assuming you're using OSS, you should configure @file{/dev/dsp} as your input and 
@file{/dev/dsp1} as output device or vice versa (@pxref{In- and Output}). 
This just depends on your local setup, but you'll hopefully know about that. 
Even better for fun is ALSA
