This time you choose the @file{alsa_audio_out} and @file{alsa_audio_in} plugins. 
In this case the device names will be something like @file{plughw:#soundcard, #subdevice}, e.g.
@file{plughw:0,0} for your first sound card in the system.
At this stage you should have a working sound setup.

@subsection The Mickey Mouse
In this section we build a easy network, that will transform your voice into Mickey Mouse
or Darth Vader. Whatever you prefer... First you go into @ref{The Main Window} and select
"New Filternetwork" from the Filternetwork menu. Then you add those three plugins to @ref{The Filternetwork Editor}:
@table @code
@item audio_in (input section), @pxref{Audio I/O}
@item audio_out (output section),@pxref{Audio I/O}
@item flanger (effects section), @pxref{Flanger}
@end table
Press the right mouse button and a popup menu will appear. Select the right plugins and drag them
around the network canvas with a simple click, drag & release. Then connect the plugins like this:@*
@code{audio_in} -> @code{flanger} -> @code{audio_out}.

