@subsection The Voice Drumloop
Now we're going for a more sophisticated network. A looping sampler that will record your voice and do an
endless loop on that sample. This way you will be able to record a drumloop just created with your voice
or other stuff you do with you microphone. This time we will need the following plugins:
@table @code
@item audio_in  (input section), @pxref{Audio I/O}
@item audio_out (output section), @pxref{Audio I/O}
@item mix       (routing section), @pxref{Junctions and Dead Ends}
@item buffer    (routing section), @pxref{Junctions and Dead Ends}
@item one2n     (routing section), @pxref{Junctions and Dead Ends}
@item delay     (time section), @pxref{Mangling Data Streams}
@end table

Now wire up the network like this:
@table @code
@item audio_in -> mix -> one2n -> audio_out
@item one2n -> buffer -> delay -> mix
@end table

