Now press with the right mouse button on the knob of the connection between delay and mix. Select
"Destination Properties" and set the gain to 1.9, you can later play with this to get better/different/weird
results. Then open up the properties for the buffer plugin and set the time parameter to 1 second. Open up
the properties for the delay plugin and set the delay time to 500ms. Now execute the network and say "Boom"
into your microphone. BEWARE: If you set the gain to high between mix and delay you get a really nice and
loud feedback. So don't turn up your stereo too loud for your first try. Play around with the gain. If you
set it too smaller values, your voice will slowly fade out, if it's to high it will just get louder and louder
and blow out your speakers. Don't blame me for trouble with your neighbours ;)
If you don't want to go through the network setup everytime, simply save the the network with the "Save" button
and load it again next time. All your parameter settings will be preserved.

